3.7.1.text: Recipient country or recipient region should be declared for either the activity or for all transactions.
8.10.2.text: The actual value should be a valid number for all non-qualitative indicator measures (e.g. 1 = unit, 2 = percentage, 3 = nominal, 4 = ordinal).
8.10.3.text: The actual value should be omitted for qualitative indicator measures.
8.8.1.text: The baseline must have a value when the indicator measure is non-qualitative (e.g. 1 = unit, 2 = percentage, 3 = nominal, 4 = ordinal).
8.8.2.text: The baseline value should be a valid number for all non-qualitative measures (e.g. 1 = unit, 2 = percentage, 3 = nominal, 4 = ordinal).
8.9.2.text: The target value should be a valid number for all non-qualitative measures (e.g. 1 = unit, 2 = percentage, 3 = nominal, 4 = ordinal)
8.9.3.text: The target value should be omitted for qualitative measures.
